<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-05T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-05T17:00:00-05:00" n="477" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d477">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">865.00/7–645: Telegram</note>
                                <head>No. 477<lb/><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in <persName corresp="#p_I2">Italy</persName>
                                    </hi> (<persName corresp="#p_KA1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    </hi><note n="1" xml:id="d477fn1">The gist of this message was
                                        included in telegram No. 11 of July 10 from <persName corresp="#p_GJC1">Grew</persName> to <persName corresp="#p_BJF1">Byrnes</persName> (file No. 740.00119
                                        Potsdam/7–1045).</note>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]<note n="2" xml:id="d477fn2">For the full text of this message, see <ref target="#d469">document No. 469</ref>.</note></seg>
                                </opener>
                                <opener>
                                    <seg rendition="#left">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                    </seg>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-06T00:00:00+02:00">July 6, 1945—midnight</date>.</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>1851. Strictly confidential.</p>
                                <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                                <p>… It must be admitted, however, that in the present circumstances
                                    no govt however gifted can prove its effectiveness unless the
                                    armistice regime is abolished[,] unless Allied troops are
                                    maintained in the country to give confidence to the people in
                                    their prevailing state of demoralization and unless material aid
                                    is immediately forthcoming to prevent unrest through widespread
                                    unemployment and undernourishment.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <persName corresp="#p_KA1">
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                                        </persName>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>